description:
**Problem**
Common pattern of "check exists, check not deleted, then unwrap later":
```rust
if repo_state.state.get_live(id).is_none() {
    if repo_state.state.get_tombstone(id).is_some() {
        return Response::err(OpError::BeadDeleted(id.clone()));
    }
    return Response::err(OpError::NotFound(id.clone()));
}
// ... later ...
let bead = repo_state.state.get_live_mut(id).unwrap();
```

**Design**
Add a combined lookup that returns the appropriate error:
```rust
pub enum LiveLookupError {
    NotFound,
    Deleted,
}

impl CanonicalState {
    pub fn require_live(&self, id: &BeadId) -> Result<&Bead, LiveLookupError> {
        if let Some(b) = self.get_live(id) {
            return Ok(b);
        }
        if self.get_tombstone(id).is_some() {
            return Err(LiveLookupError::Deleted);
        }
        Err(LiveLookupError::NotFound)
    }

    pub fn require_live_mut(&mut self, id: &BeadId) -> Result<&mut Bead, LiveLookupError> {
        // Same logic for mutable access
    }
}
```

Daemon maps `LiveLookupError` → `OpError::{NotFound, BeadDeleted}`.

**Acceptance**
- [ ] `LiveLookupError` enum in `src/core/state.rs`
- [ ] `require_live` and `require_live_mut` methods on `CanonicalState`
- [ ] Executor/query code uses these instead of check-then-unwrap pattern
- [ ] Tests for NotFound vs Deleted cases

**Files:** src/core/state.rs, src/daemon/executor.rs, src/daemon/query_executor.rs
